use git from windows command prompt

git config --global user.name "Sam Smith”

git config --global user.email sam@example.com

Git init : initializes git in the provided file path

Git add * : adds everything from the file to staging

git add filepath : adds specified file

git status : shows commit status

git commit -m “message” : commits everything on GitHub

git remote add origin https://github.com/sagarkamthane/selenium-python.git :connects local repository to GitHub

git push -u origin master : pushes all code to master branch

git clone https://github.com/sagarkamthane/selenium-python.git : clones repository from github to local machine


